description:
"Kennedy" is a news panel show hosted by Kennedy Montgomery. Kennedy Montgomery is a libertarian that you may recognize from 90's MTV, Stossel, and the Independents.

Kennedy talks about section 215 of the Patriot Act and Rand Paul. Woop filibuster! Chris Christie joins Mitch  Connell in his pro-big government ways.

Tonights panel consists of JOE DEVITO, CHARLES COOKE, and KAYLEIGH MCENANY and they stop by to discuss Obama's recent speech about how the US is finally not in a major ground war. (What a low bar for a speech.) Koch Bros. may spend as much as 900 million in cash on GOP candidates. Koch Bros. leave out social conservatives in the process. (haha)

The panel returns to discuss the DEA's secret strip club. Somestory about narcissists or whatever. I don't know. I zoned out.

KELLEY PAUL, wife of Rand Paul, stops by to discuss what life could be like when he runs in 2016, and her book "True and Constant Friends".

We welcome back the panel to discuss a recent USDA recommendation for Smores. Apparently the way to go is to remove the chocolate and marshmallow. What do you replace them with? Strawberries and yogurt. Have fun kids! Next topic. Taco Bell and Pizza hut remove artificial flavoring. No more corn syrup?! Up next, Japan has major suicide problem. The problem is so bad that the Japanese government is actually pushing vacations.

CLAY TARVER (writer on Silicon Valley) stops by to discuss Silicon Valley, and Bullet Lavolta.

On tonights nightcap, 2016 presidential election campaign schwag.
